   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Huntington_HM28608_1827_02_xx_page01.jpg"/>
            <p>I am weary of waiting for an answer from<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Lockhart</persName> - I enclose a note to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockS1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. <choice>
                     <orig>Lock-<lb/>
                  -hart</orig>
                     <reg>Lockhart</reg>
                  </choice>
               </persName> who is a kind creature &amp; I have <choice>
                  <orig>commis<lb/>
                     sioned</orig>
                  <reg>commissioned</reg>
               </choice> her to shake the table on which her<lb/>
               husband is writing or to take his darling<lb/>
               boy from him till he has penned an<lb/>
               answer to my letter - She will by these<lb/>
               or some other means get it done -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>Will you have the note delivered<lb/>
                  at their house in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK">Town</placeName> - or if they <choice>
                  <orig>sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>
                  </orig>
                  <reg>should</reg>
               </choice>
               <lb/>
                  be out of <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK">Town</placeName> have it directed &amp; forward<lb/>
               ed to wherever they are-<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>If you <choice>
                  <orig>sh.<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>
                  </orig>
                  <reg>should</reg>
               </choice> wish to be introduced to<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Lockhart</persName> &amp; to settle the business <unclear/>
               <lb/>
               let me know &amp; I will pen you a note<lb/>
               introductory - But remember I do<lb/>
               not press or <hi rend="underline">advise</hi> it - I always say<lb/>
               plainly whether I think persons would<lb/>
               suit who are about to be introduced;<lb/>
                  &amp; I do not think you &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. L</persName> would<lb/>
               suit each other - But in this I may<lb/>
               be quite wrong - I <choice>
                  <orig>sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>
                  </orig>
                  <reg>should</reg>
               </choice> have said the same<lb/>
               of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeW1">William E</persName> &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. L</persName> - yet they agreed<lb/>
               wondrous well &amp; liked each other for <hi rend="underline">two</hi>
               <lb/>
               <hi rend="underline">whole</hi> days at <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Killarney_IE"/>Killarney!! -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>I wish you would be pleased to answer<lb/>
               me about my own affair of <choice>
                  <orig>Chilian</orig>
                  <reg>Chilean</reg>
               </choice> bonds<lb/>
                  - I sent you <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MoilJ1">Moilliet</persName>s urgent letter to me advising<lb/>
               immediate sale even at the expense of<lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Huntington_HM28608_1827_02_xx_page02.jpg"/>
               
               losing half my 900£ - I told you moreover or<lb/>
                  sent you <add>the prescient</add> M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. <persName ref="./Personography.xml#RicaD1">Ricardo</persName>'s information respecting<lb/>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#CL">
                  <choice>
                     <orig>Chilian</orig>
                     <reg>Chilean</reg>
                  </choice>
               </placeName> funds - viz that the stoppage in paying<lb/>
                  the <choice>
                  <orig>div<hi rend="superscript">ds</hi>.</orig>
                  <reg>dividends</reg>
               </choice> arises from a quarrel between the<lb/>
                  merchants who supplied the loan to the <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#CL">
                  <choice>
                     <orig>Chilian</orig>
                     <reg>Chilean</reg>
                  </choice>
               </placeName>
               <choice>
                  <orig>Gov<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                  </orig>
                  <reg>Government</reg>
               </choice>
               <lb/>
                  &amp; the <choice>
                  <orig>Gov<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>.</orig>
                  <reg>Government</reg>
               </choice> - <choice>
                  <orig>The Gov<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>.</orig>
                  <reg>Government</reg>
               </choice> had promised them certain<lb/>
               commercial privileges which have not been granted<lb/>
                  &amp; they in consequence withhold money for <choice>
                  <orig>div<hi rend="superscript">ds</hi>.</orig>
                  <reg>dividends</reg>
               </choice> till<lb/>
               they are granted - If this be fact - there would be<lb/>
               reasonable hope that the quarrel might be settled<lb/>
                  &amp; the <choice>
                  <orig>div<hi rend="superscript">ds</hi>.</orig>
                  <reg>dividends</reg>
               </choice> paid in time &amp; it would be imprudent<lb/>
               in me to sell now at great loss - On the other hand<lb/>
               if the above story be only a stock exchange humbug<lb/>
               the sooner I sell the better because it is better to lose<lb/>
               half than the whole - I want you to tell me if any<lb/>
               further information has been or can be obtained - I do<lb/>
               not want to rack you to extort an opinion if you<lb/>
               cannot give one - but an answer you <hi rend="underline">can</hi> give &amp; pray do</p>
            <lb/>
            <closer>
                  ever affect<hi rend="superscript">ly</hi>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">ME</persName>
               <lb/>
               <address>
                  <addrLine>
                     <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauF1">Capt<hi rend="superscript">n</hi>.. Beaufort</persName>R.N.</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>
                     <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Manchester-Street_ENK">Manchester S<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                     </placeName>
                  </addrLine>
                  <addrLine>
                     <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK">London</placeName>
                  </addrLine>
               </address>
               <note>Edgw<hi rend="superscript">h</hi>. Affair<lb/>
                  Feb. 1827</note>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
         </div>
